place_info.title: Cravery Cafe
place_info.address: Film Nagar, Plot No 416A, Rd Number 78, Phase III, Jubilee Hills, Hyderabad, Telangana 500033, India

reviews.snippet:
Cozy place, good ambience, food tastes really good. It would be better if the portion of serving could be increased. The size of the pizza was quite small, the price to quantity ratio wasn't that satisfactory but the taste was good. We did try vegetarian options only on the menu.
This place has a collection of few books as well for reading during quick bites or solo sessions.

Surprisingly I liked rasam rice here, this place has a variety of coffee options as well. The cheese pulled garlic bread was good too. Paneer panza is also a must try.

Overall I would rate
Food taste 4.5/5
Food portion 3/5
Price ₹₹₹
Ambience 4/5
Service 5/5

reviews.snippet:
Cravery cafe is a perfect place for causal dining with family and friends. Ambience is so well designed and
The night view adds a magical touch to the overall experience, making it a perfect place to unwind.

The food menu is somewhat limited but is carefully curated and each of the dishes that we tried were high presentation and were tastefully done. The options are much more for waffles, desserts, coffee and quenchers and they are delightful.i would recommend blue berry cheese cake is the best dessert in this cafe.The tables are set with a QR code which has the menu there is a small device to call for the attender for service or for the bill.
The staff was really quick and helpful. Overall a well spent family time with yummy food.

reviews.snippet:
I recently visited a charming cafe in Hyderabad that left a lasting impression on me. The cozy ambiance with soft lighting and comfortable seating made it a perfect spot to unwind. The staff were incredibly welcoming and attentive, adding to the overall pleasant experience.

The menu offered a delightful variety of dishes and beverages. I particularly enjoyed their signature coffee blend, which was rich and flavorful. The food was well-prepared and presented beautifully, showcasing both taste and aesthetic appeal.

While the prices were slightly on the higher side, the quality of the food and service justified the cost. One area for improvement could be the waiting time for the orders, as it was a bit longer than expected.

Overall, my visit to this cafe was a delightful experience, and I would definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a cozy place to enjoy good food and drinks in Hyderabad."

reviews.snippet:
This cafe is on the list of my most favourite places to visit with friends! Their Mac&Cheese is the cheesiest and the best version I've ever had in Hyderabad. I come back here for their Mac&Cheese and mozerella sticks!
Flaky chicken popcorn, cheese pull garlic bread, grill chicken and garlic prawns are must try!

Not a fan of desserts here, pretty average.

Among the beverages, smoked Rosemary and Blueberry and Caramel Frappe are too good!

reviews.snippet:
Cozy little place that serves delicious food.

1. Hazelnut latte - Served in a big cup, quantity more than a conventional cup of coffee, tasted great. 5/5 🌟
2. Parisienne carrot and cheese soup - perfect especially on rainy days, the flavours were subtle and pleasant. 5/5 🌟
3. Peri peri chicken mac n cheese - if you’re craving for something cheesy then you must try this. Well deserved hype. 4.5/5 🌟

Prices on the higher side(except for coffee).

reviews.snippet:
If you are looking for a cafe to hangout and spend time with a friend/friends and talking over some great food - You found the right place.
My personal favourites were the Chicken Forestiere and Nawabi Chicken Panza (Reminds you of Kheema buns). If cheese and cheese pulls are what you crave - Go for the Mac n Cheeze without a second hesitation. For those with a sweet tooth the OCD Sundae is a sweetheart. Otherwise for mild sweet desert - Tres leches garnished with rose petals and nuts is great too
